Speaking about her personal style, Cosmo India’s digital coverstar @mrunalthakur shares: “I love representing our culture abroad. I recently wore a Raw Mango piece when I was travelling internationally for work." Mrunal is also a self-confessed tomboy and loves wearing bucket hat, sweatpants, and sweatshirts. 

When she gets married, Mrunal sees herself wearing her mother’s maroon shalu (a type of Banarasi sari) with a Maharashtrian nath [nose ring]. “It’s something that completes the look,” she shares. “But I gotta find the guy first! He has to be someone who respects me…”

Cosmo India's digital coverstar @mrunalthakur has a lot to look forward to this year. She has just wrapped up a Telugu film and has a bunch of films slated to release soon. “A lot is changing in the world of Indian cinema,” shares Mrunal. “South Indian films are doing very well, and language isn’t a barrier anymore. The Indian film industry is becoming more and more accepting of other languages. It’s no longer a 'Hindi' or 'Telugu' film–it’s an Indian film,” says Mrunal. “I’m very proud of entering an era where the storytelling is appreciated in all regional languages.”

“When it comes to love, I’m very old school,” shares actor Mrunal Thakur(@mrunalthakur ), who is Cosmo India's Digital Coverstar, which has been shot exclusively on the Tecno (@tecnomobileindia ) CAMON 19 series phone. 

“A love letter has so much importance in my life; and that’s what’s missing these days – our love for each other. People feel underappreciated, or don’t feel the love, or aren’t secure in relationships. I truly believe there is one person meant just for you. That’s one of the reasons I’m still single, and waiting for 'The One’.”

Presenting, a one-of-a-kind collaboration aimed to create unique experiences! Tecno (@tecnomobileindia )mobiles has joined forces with Cosmo India to create ‘stylish affair’, an exciting campaign that launches the brands CAMON 19 series phone in India. 

Merging Fashion and Technology through this distinctive alliance, TECNO brings in its tech prowess with its industry-first, key mobile camera technology, RGBW sensor that enables the camera to click the perfect portraits even in low light conditions. Equally, Cosmopolitan brings its fashion, photography, and creative expertise to the table. 

The intent is to create a unique platform for budding style icons and enthusiasts pan-India. Watch this space to know more!

Our November-December cover star Rashmika Mandanna (@rashmika_mandanna) is easily one of the most versatile young actors in the country, with a slew of blockbusters under her belt. In a heart-to-heart with Cosmo India Editor, Pratishtha Dobhal (@pratishtha_dobhal), the 28-year-old actor tells it like it is.

Excerpt from the interview:

“I think I am a manifestation of destiny. Of course there are phases in life where you think ‘I want to be an actor’ but I never thought it was a possibility. I was like, ‘Whatever comes in my life, I need to be the best at it’. It’s destiny that has got me here today—and this has come with a lot of patience, hard work, pushing my boundaries, learning everyday, and respecting my craft as an actor. So, even though I am a manifestation of destiny, I work hard for what I want.”

Head to the link in bio to read her full cover interview! And don’t forget to grab a copy of the latest Cosmo India Nov-Dec issue.

Anushka Sen (@anushkasen0408) brings all the festive feels as she celebrates her first Christmas with her adorable dogs, Bruno and Cindra, in Cosmopolitan India’s ‘Christmas with My Pets’ series. From cherishing precious firsts with Bruno to treating Cindra to her favorite snacks, this heartwarming duo makes the season extra special in their new home. Christmas is all about new memories, joy, and a whole lot of puppy love.

#CosmoIndia #CosmopolitanIndia

Rithvik Dhanjani’s (@rithvikk_dhanjani) Christmas becomes even more magical with his little buddy, Murphy, in Cosmopolitan India’s 'Christmas with My Pet' series. From creating art together to the thrill of unwrapping gifts, this duo embraces every moment of holiday cheer. With Murphy by his side, Rithvik reminds us that the true spirit of Christmas lies in sharing joy, making memories, and cherishing the small moments that make the season special.

#CosmoIndia #CosmoplitanIndia

Dhanashree Verma (@dhanashree9) brings holiday cheer to life as she celebrates Christmas with her beloved dog, Coffee, in Cosmopolitan India’s 'Christmas with My Pet' series. From upholding cherished holiday traditions to delighting Coffee with gifts like new shoes, tasty treats, and favourite toys, this festive duo perfectly captures the warmth and joy of the season.

#CosmoIndia #CosmopolitanIndia

Akansha Ranjan (@akansharanjankapoor) brings festive cheer to the holiday season alongside her furry companion, Mija, in Cosmopolitan India’s ‘Christmas with My Pet’ series. From indulging Mija with delicious treats to styling her in charming outfits, this dynamic duo radiates warmth and love. As a devoted dog mom, Akansha treasures every wag of Mija’s tail, reminding us that Christmas is about celebrating the special bonds that fill our lives with joy—our beloved pets included!

#CosmoIndia #CosmopolitanIndia

PV Sindhu (@pvsindhu1) is the epitome of grace and glamour at her Sangeet ceremony, wearing Abu Jani Sandeep Khosla. Dazzling in a self-embroidered gown paired with a matching cape, the rich green hue is brought to life with an exquisite array of bugle beads and crystals. It’s a show-stopping look that perfectly blends opulence and modern elegance.

Karishma Tanna’s (@karishmaktanna) Christmas tradition? As part of Cosmopolitan India's 'Christmas with My Pets' series, Tanna shows us how she celebrates the holiday with her partner-in-crime, Coco! Every year, she makes the season extra special by surprising her furry best friend with thoughtful gifts—because who says Santa only visits humans? From cosy cuddles by the tree to heartwarming moments that capture the magic of the holidays, this duo proves that unconditional love is the brightest light of the season.
